you see behind me

00:17:31.920 --> 00:17:34.810
are live queries
coming in from mobile.

00:17:34.810 --> 00:17:38.080
In fact, today, over
50% of our queries

00:17:38.080 --> 00:17:39.880
come from mobile phones.

00:17:39.880 --> 00:17:45.150
And the queries in color you
see behind me are voice queries.

00:17:45.150 --> 00:17:50.230
In the US, on our mobile app
and Android, 1 in 5 queries,

00:17:50.230 --> 00:17:53.510
20% of our queries,
are voice queries.

00:17:53.510 --> 00:17:55.420
And that share is growing.

00:17:55.420 --> 00:17:58.830
Given how differently
users are engaging with us,

00:17:58.830 --> 00:18:00.930
we want to push
ourselves and deliver

00:18:00.930 --> 00:18:02.990
them information,
rich information,

00:18:02.990 --> 00:18:05.370
in the context of mobile.

00:18:05.370 --> 00:18:08.420
This is why, if you come
to Google today and search

00:18:08.420 --> 00:18:11.730
for Beyonce, you don't
just get 10 blue links,

00:18:11.730 --> 00:18:14.970
you get a rich information
card with music,

00:18:14.970 --> 00:18:17.940
you can listen to her
songs, find information

00:18:17.940 --> 00:18:22.360
about upcoming show events,
and book it right there.

00:18:22.360 --> 00:18:23.810
You can come and
ask us different

00:18:23.810 --> 00:18:27.580
queries-- presidential
elections or Champions League,

00:18:27.580 --> 00:18:31.370
and we again give you
rich in-depth information.

00:18:31.370 --> 00:18:36.010
And we do this across thousands
and thousands of categories

00:18:36.010 --> 00:18:39.530
globally at scale.

00:18:39.530 --> 00:18:42.022
You can come to Google
looking for news as well.

00:18:42.022 --> 00:18:43.980
For example, if you're
interested in Hyperloop,

00:18:43.980 --> 00:18:46.380
an exciting
technology, we give you

00:18:46.380 --> 00:18:49.690
information with AMP right
there in search results.

00:18:49.690 --> 00:18:53.590
And they load instantly, and
you can scroll through them.

00:18:53.590 --> 00:18:57.070
Amazing to see how people
engage differently with Google.

00:18:57.070 --> 00:18:59.680
It's not just enough
to give them links.

00:18:59.680 --> 00:19:04.210
We really need to help them get
things done in the real world.

00:19:04.210 --> 00:19:07.330
This is why we are
evolving search

00:19:07.330 --> 00:19:10.020
to be much more assistive.

00:19:10.020 --> 00:19:13.240
We've been laying the foundation
for this for many, many years

00:19:13.240 --> 00:19:16.860
through investments in deep
areas of computer science.

00:19:16.860 --> 00:19:19.040
We built the Knowledge Graph.

00:19:19.040 --> 00:19:24.430
We, today, have an understanding
of 1 billion entities-- people,

00:19:24.430 --> 00:19:27.920
places, and things-- and the
relationships between them

00:19:27.920 --> 00:19:30.080
and the real world.

00:19:30.080 --> 00:19:32.070
We have dramatically
improved the quality

00:19:32.070 --> 00:19:34.160
of our voice recognition.

00:19:34.160 --> 00:19:38.340
We recently started training our
datasets with noisy backgrounds

00:19:38.340 --> 00:19:42.210
deliberately, so that we can
hear people more accurately.

00:19:42.210 --> 00:19:46.650
The quality is improved
recently by 25%.

00:19:46.650 --> 00:19:49.190
Image recognition
and computer vision,

00:19:49.190 --> 00:19:52.300
we can do things which we never
thought we could do before.

00:19:52.300 --> 00:19:56.470
If you're in Google Photos
today and you search for hugs,

00:19:56.470 --> 00:19:59.170
we actually pull
all the pictures

00:19:59.170 --> 00:20:03.084
of people hugging in
your personal collection.

00:20:03.084 --> 00:20:06.830
[APPLAUSE]

00:20:06.830 --> 00:20:09.460
We have recently
extended this to videos.

00:20:09.460 --> 00:20:11.930
So you can say, show
me my dog videos,

00:20:11.930 --> 00:20:13.700
and we actually go
through your videos

00:20:13.700 --> 00:20:18.470
and pull out your
favorite videos.

00:20:18.470 --> 00:20:21.990
Translation, 10
years ago, we could

00:20:21.990 --> 00:20:25.110
translate, machine-translate
in two languages.

00:20:25.110 --> 00:20:28.130
Today, we do that for
over 100 languages.

00:20:28.130 --> 00:20:32.420
And every single day, we
translate over 140 billion

00:20:32.420 --> 00:20:34.860
words for our users.

00:20:34.860 --> 00:20:37.920
We even do real time
visual translation.

00:20:37.920 --> 00:20:41.680
If you're a Chinese user and
you run into a menu in English,

00:20:41.680 --> 00:20:43.900
all you need to do is
to hold up your phone,

00:20:43.900 --> 00:20:47.770
and we can translate it
into English for you.

00:20:47.770 --> 00:20:49.820
Progress in all
of these areas is

00:20:49.820 --> 00:20:52.580
accelerating thanks
to profound advances

00:20:52.580 --> 00:20:54.350
in machine learning and AI.

00:20:54.350 --> 00:20:57.360
And I believe we are
at a seminal moment.

00:20:57.360 --> 00:20:59.210
We, as Google, have
evolved significantly

00:20:59.210 --> 00:21:01.040
over the past 10 years.

00:21:01.040 --> 00:21:03.650
And we believe we are poised
to take a big leap forward

00:21:03.650 --> 00:21:05.790
in the next 10 years.

00:21:05.790 --> 00:21:07.880
So leveraging our
state-of-the-art capabilities

00:21:07.880 --> 00:21:11.350
in machine learning and AI,
we truly want to take the next

00:21:11.350 --> 00:21:14.670
step in being more
assistive for our users.

00:21:14.670 --> 00:21:19.270
So today, we are announcing
the Google Assistant.

00:21:19.270 --> 00:21:23.590
[APPLAUSE]

00:21:24.550 --> 00:21:27.790
So what do we mean when we
say the Google Assistant?

00:21:27.790 --> 00:21:31.640
We want to be there for
our users, asking them, hi,

00:21:31.640 --> 00:21:32.970
how can I help?

00:21:32.970 --> 00:21:36.630
We think of the Assistant
in a very specific way.

00:21:36.630 --> 00:21:40.270
We think of it as a
conversational assistant.

00:21:40.270 --> 00:21:44.870
You want users to have an
ongoing two-way dialogue

00:21:44.870 --> 00:21:46.500
with Google.

00:21:46.500 --> 00:21:50.670
We want you to help get things
done in your real world.

00:21:50.670 --> 00:21:54.810
And we want to do it for you,
understanding your context,

00:21:54.810 --> 00:21:56.590
giving you control of it.

00:21:56.590 --> 00:21:59.410
We think of this as
building each user

00:21:59.410 --> 00:22:02.200
their own individual Google.

00:22:02.200 --> 00:22:05.050
We already have elements of
the Assistant working hard

00:22:05.050 --> 00:22:06.710
for our users.

00:22:06.710 --> 00:22:10.640
I mentioned earlier that 20%
of queries on our mobile app

00:22:10.640 --> 00:22:13.490
and Android in the
US are voice queries.

00:22:13.490 --> 00:22:16.640
Every single day,
people say, OK, Google

00:22:16.640 --> 00:22:19.600
and ask us questions
that we help them with.

00:22:19.600 --> 00:22:22.810
And we have started becoming
truly conversational

00:22:22.810 --> 00:22:26.350
because of our strengths in
natural language processing.

00:22:26.350 --> 00:22:30.280
For example, you can be in front
of this structure in Chicago

00:22:30.280 --> 00:22:33.170
and ask Google,
who designed this?

00:22:33.170 --> 00:22:37.050
You don't need to say the
beam or the cloud gate.

00:22:37.050 --> 00:22:40.850
Understand your context, and
we answer that the designer

00:22:40.850 --> 00:22:43.130
is Anish Kapoor.

00:22:43.130 --> 00:22:45.690
Here's another example.

00:22:45.690 --> 00:22:50.246
You can ask Google, who
directed "The Revenant"--

00:22:50.246 --> 00:22:52.120
GOOGLE ASSISTANT: "The
Revenant" was directed

00:22:52.120 --> 00:22:54.520
by Alejandro Gonzalez Inarritu.

00:22:54.520 --> 00:22:57.090
SUNDAR PICHAI: And you can
follow that up with a question,

00:22:57.090 --> 00:22:59.150
show me his awards.

00:22:59.150 --> 00:23:00.966
Notice that I didn't
say the name, which

00:23:00.966 --> 00:23:02.840
I'm glad, because I find
that name very, very

00:23:02.840 --> 00:23:03.750
hard to pronounce.

00:23:03.750 --> 00:23:05.220
[LAUGHTER]

00:23:05.220 --> 00:23:08.170
And Google could pick
that conversation up

00:23:08.170 --> 00:23:10.590
and return the right to answer.

00:23:10.590 --> 00:23:12.240
This has historically
been really

00:23:12.240 --> 00:23:14.230
hard to do for computers.

00:23:14.230 --> 00:23:15.925
The reason we are
able to do this

00:23:15.925 --> 00:23:18.330
is because we have
invested the last decade

00:23:18.330 --> 00:23:21.570
in building the world's best
natural language processing

00:23:21.570 --> 00:23:23.300
technology.

00:23:23.300 --> 00:23:26.900
And our ability to do
conversational understanding

00:23:26.900 --> 00:23:30.390
is far ahead of what
other assistants can do.

00:23:30.390 --> 00:23:33.050
Especially if you look
at follow-on queries,

00:23:33.050 --> 00:23:36.640
our studies show that we
are an order of magnitude

00:23:36.640 --> 00:23:39.250
ahead of everyone else.

00:23:39.250 --> 00:23:43.100
So today, people are using
Google and asking us questions

00:23:43.100 --> 00:23:45.100
