for creating a lot of excitement

00:28:21.030 --> 00:28:22.680
in this space.

00:28:22.680 --> 00:28:25.387
We've been thinking about
our own unique approach,

00:28:25.387 --> 00:28:27.220
and we are getting ready
to launch something

00:28:27.220 --> 00:28:28.790
later this year.

00:28:28.790 --> 00:28:31.410
To give you a preview,
I'm going to invite Mario

00:28:31.410 --> 00:28:33.367
from the Chromecast team.

00:28:33.367 --> 00:28:33.867
[APPLAUSE]

00:28:33.867 --> 00:28:38.657
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:28:42.968 --> 00:28:44.460
MARIO QUEIROZ: Thanks, Sundar.

00:28:44.460 --> 00:28:47.150
Today, we want to give
you an early preview

00:28:47.150 --> 00:28:50.950
of how we're bringing the
Google Assistant to the home.

00:28:50.950 --> 00:28:55.000
Our aspiration is to make the
Assistant useful and enjoyable

00:28:55.000 --> 00:28:58.150
in one of the most important
places in your world,

00:28:58.150 --> 00:29:00.930
where you spend time
with your family.

00:29:00.930 --> 00:29:03.250
When I walk into
my house, I want

00:29:03.250 --> 00:29:06.630
to be able to continue to have
access to the Google Assistant.

00:29:06.630 --> 00:29:10.840
But I should be able to interact
with it in a hands-free way

00:29:10.840 --> 00:29:16.270
simply using my voice without
having to take out my phone.

00:29:16.270 --> 00:29:20.590
This is why we're creating
Google Home, a device which

00:29:20.590 --> 00:29:24.920
will be available
later this year.

00:29:24.920 --> 00:29:28.700
Google Home lets you enjoy
music and entertainment

00:29:28.700 --> 00:29:32.810
throughout your entire
house, manage everyday tasks

00:29:32.810 --> 00:29:38.130
more easily, and ask Google
what you want to know.

00:29:38.130 --> 00:29:42.080
All of this will be done by
speaking with the Assistant.

00:29:42.080 --> 00:29:45.810
It will let anyone in the
family, kids or adults,

00:29:45.810 --> 00:29:48.500
have a conversation with Google.

00:29:48.500 --> 00:29:52.112
Google Home is unmatched in
far-field voice recognition,

00:29:52.112 --> 00:29:55.440
since it's powered by more
than 10 years of innovation

00:29:55.440 --> 00:29:58.040
in natural language processing.

00:29:58.040 --> 00:30:01.130
I can continue the two-way
dialogue with the Assistant

00:30:01.130 --> 00:30:03.730
that Sundar mentioned
earlier, whether I'm

00:30:03.730 --> 00:30:06.420
standing nearby cooking
dinner or sitting

00:30:06.420 --> 00:30:11.170
across the room playing
a game with my daughter.

00:30:11.170 --> 00:30:14.270
With Google Home, we set
out to create and design

00:30:14.270 --> 00:30:16.940
a beautiful product
that's warm and inviting

00:30:16.940 --> 00:30:20.050
and fits naturally in
many areas of the home.

00:30:20.050 --> 00:30:23.450
We're designing the top
to blend into your home.

00:30:23.450 --> 00:30:25.610
We'll give you the option
to customize the base

00:30:25.610 --> 00:30:27.640
with different
colors and finishes,

00:30:27.640 --> 00:30:31.750
including metal and fabric,
to reflect your home style,

00:30:31.750 --> 00:30:34.130
whether it be in the
living room, the kitchen,

00:30:34.130 --> 00:30:35.930
or the bedroom.

00:30:35.930 --> 00:30:38.320
We're putting a lot
of craftsmanship

00:30:38.320 --> 00:30:42.480
into the hardware design,
including the LED's placement

00:30:42.480 --> 00:30:44.820
and choreography,
the speaker that's

00:30:44.820 --> 00:30:48.490
going to fill the room you're
in with music, the microphone

00:30:48.490 --> 00:30:52.930
system, and the clean
face without any buttons.

00:30:57.678 --> 00:31:02.016
[APPLAUSE]

00:31:03.470 --> 00:31:06.520
This is Google Home.

00:31:06.520 --> 00:31:08.780
We think it'll be a
beautiful addition

00:31:08.780 --> 00:31:11.610
to any room in your house.

00:31:11.610 --> 00:31:14.490
And we're even more
excited about what

00:31:14.490 --> 00:31:15.610
it's going to do for you.

00:31:21.110 --> 00:31:23.670
First, music and
entertainment are

00:31:23.670 --> 00:31:27.870
a big part of what makes being
at home relaxing and fun.

00:31:27.870 --> 00:31:31.230
Not long ago, we
introduced Chromecast,

00:31:31.230 --> 00:31:34.920
designed to play your
favorite shows, movies,

00:31:34.920 --> 00:31:38.400
and YouTube videos on the
biggest screen in your house.

00:31:38.400 --> 00:31:41.160
Last year, we added
Chromecast Audio

00:31:41.160 --> 00:31:45.130
to bring the music you
love to your best speakers.

00:31:45.130 --> 00:31:48.530
Chromecast has been one of
the hottest-selling consumer

00:31:48.530 --> 00:31:52.100
electronics products
since the day it launched.

00:31:52.100 --> 00:31:56.510
And Google Home will build
on those experiences.

00:31:56.510 --> 00:32:00.710
Google Home is a Wi-Fi speaker
that streams music directly

00:32:00.710 --> 00:32:04.750
from the cloud, so you get
the highest quality playback.

00:32:04.750 --> 00:32:08.130
It will deliver rich
bass and clear highs

00:32:08.130 --> 00:32:12.360
all from a beautiful,
compact form factor.

00:32:12.360 --> 00:32:17.920
Of course, you can access songs,
playlists, albums, artists,

00:32:17.920 --> 00:32:21.830
and podcasts from your
favorite music services

00:32:21.830 --> 00:32:23.910
just by asking with your voice.

00:32:23.910 --> 00:32:28.350
Or if you prefer, you can send
music from your Android or iOS

00:32:28.350 --> 00:32:32.660
device through Google Cast.

00:32:32.660 --> 00:32:35.260
And unlike other
home assistants,

00:32:35.260 --> 00:32:38.120
Google Cast Support
allows you to control

00:32:38.120 --> 00:32:43.110
other speakers in your home
without complicated setup.

00:32:43.110 --> 00:32:46.050
So when you want to listen
to Coldplay in the living

00:32:46.050 --> 00:32:48.010
room on the living
room speakers,

00:32:48.010 --> 00:32:51.910
you can simply say, play "Viva
La Vida" in the living room,

00:32:51.910 --> 00:32:53.980
and it'll start playing.

00:32:53.980 --> 00:32:58.530
Cast Support also enables
multi-room playback,

00:32:58.530 --> 00:33:01.240
so that you can add
one or more Google home

00:33:01.240 --> 00:33:05.260
devices to a group of
speakers and really blast

00:33:05.260 --> 00:33:07.790
your favorite tunes.

00:33:07.790 --> 00:33:10.590
And it lets you control
your video content, too.

00:33:10.590 --> 00:33:12.850
Let's say that you want to
watch that episode of Jimmy

00:33:12.850 --> 00:33:15.860
Kimmel or the trendy
YouTube video on your TV.

00:33:15.860 --> 00:33:18.140
Just tell Google
Home, and the content

00:33:18.140 --> 00:33:21.405
that will appear on the biggest,
brightest screen in your house.

00:33:24.120 --> 00:33:28.320
Next, Google Home will become
more and more of a control

00:33:28.320 --> 00:33:30.710
center for your whole home.

00:33:30.710 --> 00:33:34.560
Home is where lots of daily
tasks just need to get done.

00:33:34.560 --> 00:33:37.020
Having access to
the Google assistant

00:33:37.020 --> 00:33:39.260
makes this a lot easier.

00:33:39.260 --> 00:33:42.250
It's like having a
voice-activated remote control

00:33:42.250 --> 00:33:44.990
to the real world
whenever you need it.

00:33:44.990 --> 00:33:48.850
You can do the basics like
setting alarms and timers,

00:33:48.850 --> 00:33:52.510
or managing to-do lists
and shopping list.

00:33:52.510 --> 00:33:56.710
We're also designing Google
Home to connect your smart home

00:33:56.710 --> 00:33:58.000
seamlessly.

00:33:58.000 --> 00:34:02.050
It will support the most
popular home networking systems,

00:34:02.050 --> 00:34:06.190
so that you can easily control
your lights, thermostats,

00:34:06.190 --> 00:34:11.060
switches, and more, including
our own Nest devices.

00:34:11.060 --> 00:34:13.870
Further in the future,
we'll work with developers

00:34:13.870 --> 00:34:16.969
to make it possible to
control things beyond the home

00:34:16.969 --> 00:34:21.000
like booking a car, ordering
dinner, or sending flowers

00:34:21.000 --> 00:34:26.699
to mom, and much, much more,
all with just your voice.

00:34:26.699 --> 00:34:32.170
Third, Google Home lets you
ask Google about anything

00:34:32.170 --> 00:34:33.710
you want to know.

00:34:33.710 --> 00:34:36.219
Of course, you
can get the basics

00:34:36.219 --> 00:34:41.150
like the weather or facts that
you might find on Wikipedia.

00:34:41.150 --> 00:34:43.909
But what makes Google
Home really shine

00:34:43.909 --> 00:34:47.260
is that it has search built in.

00:34:47.260 --> 00:34:50.449
It draws on 17
years of innovation

00:34:50.449 --> 00:34:52.969
in organizing the
world's information

00:34:52.969 --> 00:34:57.110
to answer questions which are
difficult for other assistants

00:34:57.110 --> 00:34:58.290
to handle.

00:34:58.290 --> 00:35:01.980
You might ask, how much
fat is in an avocado,

00:35:01.980 --> 00:35:05.770
or what is Draymond
Green's jersey number,

00:35:05.770 --> 00:35:08.400
and then follow up that
last question with,

00:35:08.400 --> 00:35:10.400
where did he go to college?

00:35:10.400 --> 00:35:12.390
Or try something more complex.

00:35:12.390 --> 00:35:16.671
What was the US population
when NASA was established?

00:35:16.671 --> 00:35:23.280
You will get immediate, accurate
answers from Google each time.

00:35:23.280 --> 00:35:25.010
And the Google
assistant not only

00:35:25.010 --> 00:35:28.800
knows a lot about the world,
but it will stand apart

00:35:28.800 --> 00:35:30.840
in how it can also
get to know you

00:35:30.840 --> 00:35:33.940
over time, with your
permission, of course.

00:35:33.940 --> 00:35:37.860
It can help you retrieve
your travel itinerary,

00:35:37.860 --> 00:35:41.640
your daily schedule,
your traffic to work,

00:35:41.640 --> 00:35:45.220
your package delivery
information, and much more.

00:35:45.220 --> 00:35:50.400
And as Google keeps getting
better, so will Google Home.

00:35:50.400 --> 00:35:55.170
So that's Google Home-- a
beautiful, smart, voice-enabled

00:35:55.170 --> 00:35:58.200
assistant for the whole family.

00:35:58.200 --> 00:36:01.540
Enjoy music and entertainment
throughout your entire house,

00:36:01.540 --> 00:36:05.000
manage everyday
tasks effortlessly,

00:36:05.000 --> 00:36:08.050
and ask Google what
you want to know.

