Now let's talk a bit about
privacy and security.

00:56:29.340 --> 00:56:33.830
We realize that sometimes
people want to be incognito.

00:56:33.830 --> 00:56:36.850
Of course, this applies
to chat as well.

00:56:36.850 --> 00:56:39.610
So following in the
footsteps of Chrome,

00:56:39.610 --> 00:56:43.930
we've created an
incognito mode for Allo.

00:56:43.930 --> 00:56:47.140
While all messages in
Allo are encrypted,

00:56:47.140 --> 00:56:51.460
chats in incognito mode
are end-to-end encrypted.

00:56:51.460 --> 00:56:54.530
Incognito chats have
discrete notifications,

00:56:54.530 --> 00:56:56.595
hiding the sender and
the message contents

00:56:56.595 --> 00:57:00.260
from shoulder surfers
and prying eyes.

00:57:00.260 --> 00:57:03.570
Incognito also offers
message expiration,

00:57:03.570 --> 00:57:07.190
so you're in control of how
long your private messages stick

00:57:07.190 --> 00:57:08.840
around.

00:57:08.840 --> 00:57:12.700
And similar to when you close
an Incognito window in Chrome,

00:57:12.700 --> 00:57:15.430
when you delete an incognito
conversation in Allo,

00:57:15.430 --> 00:57:17.850
it's gone forever and no
one could see it again

00:57:17.850 --> 00:57:20.290
on your device.

00:57:20.290 --> 00:57:22.490
With incognito mode,
Allo gives users

00:57:22.490 --> 00:57:26.350
additional controls over
their privacy and security.

00:57:26.350 --> 00:57:29.160
And we anticipate adding even
more security features to it

00:57:29.160 --> 00:57:31.120
over time.

00:57:31.120 --> 00:57:33.320
So that's Allo.

00:57:33.320 --> 00:57:36.060
Allo is fast, smart,
and secure, and it

00:57:36.060 --> 00:57:38.940
lets you express yourself
in fun, new ways.

00:57:38.940 --> 00:57:41.700
And Allo will be the first
home for the Google assistant

00:57:41.700 --> 00:57:45.140
as it starts to take shape,
bringing the richness of Google

00:57:45.140 --> 00:57:47.530
right into your chats.

00:57:47.530 --> 00:57:51.340
Now, Allo is all
about messaging,

00:57:51.340 --> 00:57:56.380
but let me talk to you a
minute about video calling.

00:57:56.380 --> 00:57:58.490
Just as technology has
helped connect people

00:57:58.490 --> 00:58:01.500
through messaging,
video calling has

00:58:01.500 --> 00:58:06.340
brought families and friends
together from around the world.

00:58:06.340 --> 00:58:09.130
It can be a magical experience.

00:58:09.130 --> 00:58:12.330
So why don't we pick up the
phone and do it more often?

00:58:12.330 --> 00:58:18.590
Well, maybe the other person
has a different kind of phone.

00:58:18.590 --> 00:58:22.400
Maybe the connection
is a little spotty.

00:58:22.400 --> 00:58:26.310
And even when it does
work, getting a call

00:58:26.310 --> 00:58:29.650
can often feel intrusive,
because you're not quite sure

00:58:29.650 --> 00:58:32.540
why the other person's calling.

00:58:32.540 --> 00:58:34.050
That's why we
challenged ourselves

00:58:34.050 --> 00:58:37.720
to design a video
calling experience that

00:58:37.720 --> 00:58:41.010
would feel magical every time.

00:58:41.010 --> 00:58:44.760
So I'd like to
introduce you to Duo,

00:58:44.760 --> 00:58:48.370
a simple, one-to-one video
calling app for everyone.

