01:01:03.360 --> 01:01:07.220
Now, Knock Knock only works
when the video is instant.

01:01:07.220 --> 01:01:09.560
There can't be a gap
between the phone ringing

01:01:09.560 --> 01:01:11.400
and the video appearing.

01:01:11.400 --> 01:01:14.350
This is a really hard
technical problem,

01:01:14.350 --> 01:01:17.740
but we're uniquely
positioned to tackle it.

01:01:17.740 --> 01:01:21.340
Duo was built by the
team that created WebRTC,

01:01:21.340 --> 01:01:24.550
the open-source platform that
now powers much of today's

01:01:24.550 --> 01:01:26.490
mobile video communication.

01:01:26.490 --> 01:01:30.130
And we know this technology
like no one else.

01:01:30.130 --> 01:01:32.260
We used a new
protocol called Quick

01:01:32.260 --> 01:01:35.350
that allows Duo to establish
an encrypted connection

01:01:35.350 --> 01:01:37.170
in a single round trip.

01:01:37.170 --> 01:01:40.890
We obsessed over every last
detail of video transmission,

01:01:40.890 --> 01:01:44.340
hand-tuning and optimizing
codecs, bandwidth probing,

01:01:44.340 --> 01:01:46.760
encryption, and more.

01:01:46.760 --> 01:01:49.980
The result is the unique
feel of Knock Knock.

01:01:49.980 --> 01:01:52.000
You're right there
in an instant.

01:01:54.770 --> 01:01:58.600
So the other thing that
really sets Duo apart

01:01:58.600 --> 01:02:02.550
is how reliable it
makes video calling.

01:02:02.550 --> 01:02:05.200
Duo works wherever
you are, whether it's

01:02:05.200 --> 01:02:09.210
