01:27:45.020 --> 01:27:46.890
So we've talked
about smartphones

01:27:46.890 --> 01:27:49.480
and operating systems,
headsets and controllers.

01:27:49.480 --> 01:27:52.310
But ultimately, that's
not what VR is about.

01:27:52.310 --> 01:27:54.640
It's about what
you can experience.

01:27:54.640 --> 01:27:58.230
So let's turn to apps,
what you can do in VR.

01:27:58.230 --> 01:27:59.850
Now first, if
you're a developer,

01:27:59.850 --> 01:28:02.700
you know that there's a
lot upstream from someone

01:28:02.700 --> 01:28:04.430
using your app or
playing your game.

01:28:04.430 --> 01:28:06.300
Users have to find
it in a store,

01:28:06.300 --> 01:28:08.740
buy it, install it, launch it.

01:28:08.740 --> 01:28:11.930
This will all work
seamlessly in Daydream.

01:28:11.930 --> 01:28:15.770
And that's because we've
built Google Play for VR.

01:28:15.770 --> 01:28:19.120
Users will be able to browse
and search and buy and install

01:28:19.120 --> 01:28:21.230
VR apps in VR.

01:28:21.230 --> 01:28:22.660
And once you've
installed an app,

01:28:22.660 --> 01:28:24.360
you can keep coming
back to it from what

01:28:24.360 --> 01:28:26.800
we call Daydream
Home, which gives you

01:28:26.800 --> 01:28:29.910
access to all of your
favorite games and apps.

01:28:29.910 --> 01:28:31.800
Let's actually talk
about some of those apps,

01:28:31.800 --> 01:28:35.102
the things you can do and
the places you can go.

01:28:35.102 --> 01:28:37.310
Our partners, like the "New
York Times" and the "Wall

01:28:37.310 --> 01:28:39.860
Street Journal" and CNN
are bringing their VR apps

01:28:39.860 --> 01:28:40.360
to Daydream.

01:28:40.360 --> 01:28:43.110
So you'll be able to
experience the world's news

01:28:43.110 --> 01:28:45.110
like you're actually there.

01:28:45.110 --> 01:28:49.560
Hulu, Netflix, HBO, even iMacs
are bringing their libraries

01:28:49.560 --> 01:28:50.100
to Daydream.

01:28:50.100 --> 01:28:52.490
So you'll be able to
watch shows and movies

01:28:52.490 --> 01:28:55.490
in a virtual cinema or
an immersive 3D film

01:28:55.490 --> 01:28:57.360
in a virtual IMAX theater.

01:28:57.360 --> 01:29:00.220
Here's a shot from just one
of the dozens of IMAX films

01:29:00.220 --> 01:29:01.430
