the streets of the world

01:29:44.950 --> 01:29:47.820
without having to
fly around the world.

01:29:47.820 --> 01:29:50.400
And Google Photos will
support VR photos,

01:29:50.400 --> 01:29:54.470
so you can step inside and
relive favorite moments.

01:29:54.470 --> 01:29:57.410
And there's one more-- YouTube.

01:29:57.410 --> 01:30:01.900
We've rebuilt YouTube
from the ground up for VR.

01:30:01.900 --> 01:30:04.900
In it is voice
search, discovery,

01:30:04.900 --> 01:30:07.850
your favorite playlists,
again all in VR.

01:30:07.850 --> 01:30:10.980
We've added spatial audio,
improved VR video streaming.

01:30:10.980 --> 01:30:13.620
So you'll be able to step
inside the world's largest

01:30:13.620 --> 01:30:16.740
collection of VR videos and
experience places and concerts

01:30:16.740 --> 01:30:19.410
and events like
you're actually there.

01:30:19.410 --> 01:30:21.550
And by the way, you'll
also be able to watch

01:30:21.550 --> 01:30:24.750
every single standard
video currently on YouTube,

01:30:24.750 --> 01:30:26.200
but in a very different way.

01:30:26.200 --> 01:30:28.850
And we think people
are going to love it.

01:30:28.850 --> 01:30:30.600
So that's Daydream--
our platform

01:30:30.600 --> 01:30:33.940
for high quality
mobile virtual reality,

01:30:33.940 --> 01:30:37.200
Daydream-ready smartphones
with VR optimizations as part

01:30:37.200 --> 01:30:39.490
of Android N, a
comfortable headset,

01:30:39.490 --> 01:30:41.910
and a powerful,
intuitive controller,

01:30:41.910 --> 01:30:44.820
and some amazing
apps and experiences,

01:30:44.820 --> 01:30:49.990
all designed in concert and open
and at the scale of Android.

01:30:49.990 --> 01:30:52.160
Now, Daydream arrives this fall.

